.TH "sdio_writeb_readb" 9 "sdio_writeb_readb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sdio_writeb_readb \- write and read a byte from SDIO function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u8" sdio_writeb_readb
.BI "(struct sdio_func *func "  ","
.BI "u8 write_byte "  ","
.BI "unsigned int addr "  ","
.BI "int *err_ret "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "func" 12
SDIO function to access
.IP "write_byte" 12
byte to write
.IP "addr" 12
address to write to
.IP "err_ret" 12
optional status value from transfer

Performs a RAW (Read after Write) operation as defined by SDIO spec -
single byte is written to address space of a given SDIO function and
response is read back from the same address, both using single request.
If there is a problem with the operation, 0xff is returned and
\fIerr_ret\fP will contain the error code.
